node.text:
This method to cook eggs is genius! You've never seen anything like this!

INGREDIENTS
250g (2 cups) flour
1 tsp salt
120ml (2/3 cup) water
4 tbsp oil
100 g melted butter
6 eggs

METHOD
In a bowl mix together water, oil, salt and flour. Let the dough rest for 30 minutes. Divide the dough into 6 pieces and roll out each.
Spread with melted butter and roll the dough. Roll out again for a little. Fry it in the pan on medium heat adding the egg into each bread.

node.text:
Ever tried to fry pasta? You'll fall in love with this recipe! 
 
INGREDIENTS
Paccheri pasta
Ricotta
Cooked ham
Provolone
Parmesan
3 eggs
Breadcrumbs
Salt
Pepper
Oil

METHOD
Boil the pasta for 10 minutes and let it cool.
Mix ricotta, diced ham, cheese, salt, pepper, and parmesan in a bowl. Place the mixture in a piping bag.
Fill each piece of pasta with the mixture.
Beat 3 eggs, add salt, then dip the filled pasta in the egg and cover very well with bread crumbs. Coat twice.
Use a toothpick to check that the oil is hot and fry the pasta.

node.text:
This is the most incredible way to fry an #eggplant!

INGREDIENTS
Eggplants
Salt
Water
Tapioca flour
Oil

METHOD
Peel an eggplant. Cut into large chunks.
Form a grid on each piece without cutting it all together.
Add salt to a bowl with water and place each piece of eggplant and wait for 20 minutes.
Cover each piece with flour. Deep fry with very hot oil.
Serve with sour cream.

node.text:
A simple method to make amazing fluffy #bread!

INGREDIENTS
400ml (1 3/4 cup) Milk
7g dry yeast
2 tbsp sugar
600g (4 cups) Flour
1 tsp salt
30ml (2 1/4 tbsp) Oil
Butter
Apricot jam

METHOD
In a bowl mix together warm milk with sugar and yeast, add flour and salt. Let the dough rise for about 40 minutes.
Divide the dough into 8 pieces.
Boil in hot water for 3 minutes from both sides.
Transfer to the baking pan and bake for 20 minutes at 200’C(390’F).
Serve with butter and jam.

node.text:
Kids will love these amazing bi-color #muffins: easy and fluffy! 
 
INGREDIENTS
1 egg
50g sugar
8g vanilla sugar
60ml oil
100ml milk
160g flour
8g baking powder
1 tbsp cacao powder
3 tbsp milk
Almond slices

METHOD
Pour an egg into a bowl, add sugar, vanilla sugar and mix well.
Add oil, milk and mix well.
Mix flour with baking powder and pour into the previous mixture.
Mix cocoa and milk in another bowl. Add half of the mixture to get two different colors.
Pour a little of each mixture into each hole of a muffin tray to make two-color muffins and add almond slices.
Bake for 25 minutes at 180°C (356°F).

node.text:
Beautiful and delicious, these #crepes are just amazing! 
 
INGREDIENTS
2 eggs
100g (3/4 cup) Flour
230ml (1 cup) water
1 tbsp olive oil
1/2 tsp salt
1/3 tsp pepper
8-10 zucchini Flowers
150g baked ham
100g mozzarella cheese

METHOD
In a bowl mix together eggs with salt, pepper, flour, water, oil.
Make pancakes onto the prepared pan and put the flower on top. Fry from both sides.
Fill with baked ham slices and mozzarella slices.

node.text:
The recipe to make amazing #crepes every time!

INGREDIENTS
3 eggs
2g (½ tsp) salt
10g (2 tsp) sugar
125g (1 cup) flour
250ml (1 cup) milk
12ml (1 tbsp) oil
 
Filling:
Honey
Coconut grains
 
METHOD
Add eggs, sugar, salt to the mixing bowl. Whisk with a mixer.
Add milk, oil, and sifted flour. Mix. Rest for 30 minutes.
Bake on an oiled pan.
Serve with coconut grains and honey.

node.text:
These #hashbrowns will be gone in SECONDS!

INGREDIENTS
3 potatoes
1 egg
12g (2 tbsp) cornstarch
4g (1 tsp) salt
4g (1 tsp) garlic powder
oil
 
METHOD
Boil the potatoes for 8-10 minutes. Grate the potatoes.
Add egg, starch, salt, and garlic. Mix.
Shape fritters and place them in the freezer for 30 minutes.
Fry in hot oil. Serve.

node.text:
You have never tried an #omelet this tasty!

INGREDIENTS
Red bell pepper
Yellow bell pepper
6 eggs
50g parmesan
Chives
Garlic
Thyme
Extra virgin olive oil
Salt
Pepper
Butter

METHOD
Add minced garlic and oil to a pan. Sprinkle over dried thyme. Cut the peppers, add to the pan, and cook. Then add chives
Pour 6 eggs into a bowl, add Parmesan cheese and mix thoroughly
Add the pepper mixture to the bowl with the egg and mix well.
Pour the mixture into a pan and cook on both sides to get an omelet.

node.text:
This #chocolatepudding is so creamy and irresistible!

INGREDIENTS
1l (4 cups) milk
2 egg yolks
1 cup flour
1 cup sugar
2 tbsp cocoa powder
1 tbsp butter
1 tsp vanilla sugar
1/2 cup chocolate
240ml (1 cup) water
Biscuits
 
METHOD
Into the pan add egg yolks, flour, cocoa powder, sugar, and milk, cook on low heat until thick. Add in butter, chocolate, and vanilla extract. Turn off the heat and pour in water.
Layout biscuits on the bottom of each plate. Cover them with prepared chocolate mixture, and repeat it again. Refrigerate for 1 hour, sprinkle with more chocolate chips.

node.text:
Just eggs, veggies and a muffin pan to make an incredible dinner! 😍😍

INGREDIENTS
Butter
1 onion
Garlic
Carrots
Red pepper
Leeks
4 eggs
80ml (1/3 cup) milk
Parmesan
Salt
Black pepper
Extra virgin olive oil
 
METHOD
Melt the butter in a frying pan. Then add grated garlic, carrot, onion, red pepper, leek, salt, pepper, and mix. Put in a bowl once cooked.
Mix the eggs and milk in a bowl, add salt and pepper, then add the cooked vegetables and mix well.
Brush some oil over the muffin tray then pour in the egg mixture. Cook for 15 minutes at 200ºC (392ºF).

node.text:
This idea is so cute, perfect to surprise everyone with a few basic ingredients! 

INGREDIENTS
320g (2.5 cups) flour
3 tbsp sugar
1/2 tsp salt
7g dry yeast
190ml (3/4 cup) warm milk
1 egg
1 egg yolk
3 tbsp soft butter
Salami slices
Cheese slices

METHOD
Mix together warm milk with sugar and yeast, add in the egg and soft butter, mix everything well and let the dough rise for about 2 hours.
Roll out the dough cut into strips, top with salami and cheese.
Wrap them and spread with egg yolk. Bake at 180°C (350°F) for 40 minutes.

node.text:
This treat is just delicious! Try it 😍

INGREDIENTS
For the batter:
180g (3/4 cup) of butter
25g (2 tbsp) of sugar
Salt
300g (2 cups) of flour
1 egg
 
For the filling:
1 egg
25g (3 tbsp) of powdered sugar
45ml (3 tbsp) of vegetable oil
Salt
4g (1 tsp) of vanilla sugar
45g (3 tbsp) of flour
8g (1 tbsp) of cocoa powder
4g (1 tsp) of baking powder
30g (3 tbsp) of melted chocolate
 
Powdered sugar

METHOD
In a bowl add the butter, sugar, salt, flour and mix well together with hands. Add the egg and continue to combine with your hands to make a dough.
Roll out the dough and divide it into 12 equal pieces. Add each piece to a muffin tin and arrange it to create a muffin shape.
Pierce each muffin with a fork and bake in the oven at 356 ° F / 180 ° C for about 15 minutes.
In another bowl, add egg, powdered sugar, vegetable oil, salt, vanilla sugar and mix together. Sift flour, cocoa powder, baking powder over a bowl and mix everything well. Finally, add the melted chocolate and combine everything.
Fill each batter with the chocolate mixture and bake in the oven at 356°F/180°C
for about 25 minutes
Decorate with powdered sugar.

node.text:
Salami flowers: a tasty recipe with few ingredients! 😍

INGREDIENTS
600g mashed potatoes
150g cream cheese
7g (2 tbsp) dill, chopped
black pepper to taste
150 g (5 oz) salami, sliced
Cherry tomatoes halved
30 ml (2 tbsp) olive oil

METHOD
Cook potatoes in salted boiling water for 20-30 minutes, then mash them and let cool a bit (you can also use leftover mashed potatoes). Preheat the oven to 180C/360F.
Add cream cheese, dill, and pepper, mix well until you get a homogeneous mixture.
Grease muffin tray molds with olive oil.
Arrange 4 salami slices into each muffin slot.
Place a tablespoon of potato mixture between salami slices, to obtain a “flower”. Continue to make such “flowers” until you use all of the remaining ingredients.
Cut cherry tomatoes in half and put a half on top of each “flower”.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.

node.text:
Super fluffy, the secret is here:

INGREDIENTS
470g (2 1/2 cups) of strong white flour (bread flour)
10g (2 tsp) salt
40g (3 tbsp) of sugar
7g of dried fast action yeast
4 large eggs
100ml (1/3 cup + 2 tbsp) of milk
175g (3/4 cup) softened butter
1 egg for the egg wash
Jam

METHOD
In a bowl add the flour, sugar, salt, yeast, and mix. Add the eggs, milk and combine them all together to create the dough. Add the butter and mix to create the smooth dough.
Grease another bowl with the butter and add the dough. Cover with foil and let it rest for 2 hours, or until it's doubled.
Roll out the dough and divide it into 7 equal pieces. Gently make the balls and add them to the pre-greased baking pan. Cover with foil and let it rest for about 60 minutes.
Brush with egg and bake for 35 minutes at 284°F/140°C.

node.text:
Bechamel potatoes: a unique recipe ready in no time! 😍

INGREDIENTS
5 potatoes
Olive oil
Ground red paprika
Pepper
Salt
1 onion
Garlic
300g minced meat
1 red bell pepper
1 green bell pepper
Bechamel sauce
200g of cheddar cheese
Cherry tomatoes

METHOD
Cut the potatoes into slices and arrange them into the pan covered with a baking sheet. Season them with the oil, salt, pepper, ground red paprika, and bake in the oven at 392°F/200°C for 20 minutes.
In a pot add the onion, garlic, meat, red and green peppers, and fry. Season the meat mixture with salt, pepper, and ground red paprika.
In a pan arrange the first layer of the potatoes and add the meat on top. Add the second layer of the potatoes and cover with the bechamel sauce.
Add the cheddar cheese and cherry tomatoes on top. Bake at 392°F/200°C for 30 minutes.

node.text:
This method to cook eggs is genius! You've never seen anything like this!

INGREDIENTS
250g (2 cups) flour
1 tsp salt
120ml (2/3 cup) water
4 tbsp oil
100 g melted butter
6 eggs

METHOD
In a bowl mix together water, oil, salt and flour. Let the dough rest for 30 minutes. Divide the dough into 6 pieces and roll out each.
Spread with melted butter and roll the dough. Roll out again for a little. Fry it in the pan on medium heat adding the egg into each bread.

node.text:
Ever tried to fry pasta? You'll fall in love with this recipe! 
 
INGREDIENTS
Paccheri pasta
Ricotta
Cooked ham
Provolone
Parmesan
3 eggs
Breadcrumbs
Salt
Pepper
Oil

METHOD
Boil the pasta for 10 minutes and let it cool.
Mix ricotta, diced ham, cheese, salt, pepper, and parmesan in a bowl. Place the mixture in a piping bag.
Fill each piece of pasta with the mixture.
Beat 3 eggs, add salt, then dip the filled pasta in the egg and cover very well with bread crumbs. Coat twice.
Use a toothpick to check that the oil is hot and fry the pasta.

node.text:
How to make the best homemade #applejam jam!

INGREDIENTS
2kg of apple
600g (3 cups) of sugar
100ml (1/2 cup) of water
Bread
Butter

METHOD
Clean the middle of the apple and cut it into small cubes.
In a pan add the water and add the previously cut apple cubes. Cover with a lid a cook until the apples are soft.
Mix the apples with an immersion blender until soft. Sift the apple mixture and transfer it to the pan.
Add the sugar and cook over medium heat for 1 hour.
Transfer the jam to the jars. Cover the jars with a lid and turn them over to create a vacuum.

node.text:
This is the best #chocolatecake ever! 🤤❤

INGREDIENTS
• 3 eggs
• 150g / 1 cup sugar
• 150g / 1 cup flour
• 30g cocoa
• 120ml / 4.2oz water
• 1 tsp baking powder
• 400ml / 14.1oz milk
• 2-3 tbsp corn starch
• 395g / 2.6 cups condensed milk
• 4 tbsp cocoa
• 200ml / 7oz cream cheese
• 50g chocolate
• 150g chocolate
• cream
METHOD
Beat eggs and sugar with a mixer. Add flour, cocoa, baking powder, a little water and mix. Pour dough into a piece of parchment paper. Bake for 40 minutes at 180 ° C / 350 ° F.
Add corn starch to the milk. Mix. Add condensed milk, cocoa, cream cheese, chocolate and mix. Brew cream over low heat.
Finished biscuit cut in half. Soak one layer of biscuit with condensed milk, diluted with water. Put cream on top. Cover with a second biscuit and soak it with condensed milk. Cool for 4 hours.
150 grams of chocolate mixed with cream. Brew ganache. Pour on the finished cake. Sprinkle with chocolate chips on top.

Season with salt, pepper, and parmesan.
Serve with mayonnaise.
